# Jesse's harvester fork — LiveKit signaling websocket (wss://). Host-matched inside the
# wildcard *.staging.applepie.company block, so this fragment just host-matches and
# proxies (the wildcard cert covers it). Backend (../harvester/) publishes on host
# loopback 127.0.0.1:17880, forwarded into this container by applepie.pod's `-T,17880`
# pasta entry. Caddy upgrades the WebSocket transparently and never buffers/caps it.
#
# ONLY the signaling channel rides this vhost. The media itself (ICE-TCP 7881) rides the
# layer4 forward in ../Caddyfile, not this reverse_proxy — LiveKit advertises this node's
# tailnet IP in ICE candidates (--node-ip) and browsers dial it directly. The app's
# LIVEKIT_PUBLIC_URL (../harvester/config/harvester.env) points at this name.
@livekit-harvester host livekit-harvester.staging.applepie.company
handle @livekit-harvester {
	reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:17880
}
